FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1777065069
OL,3,CCreeslough petrol station plan sparks
OL,4,Canger
OL,6,FThe mother of the youngest victim has
OL,7,Fbranded Donegal County Council's
OL,8,Fdecision to grant planning permission
OL,9,Ffor a new shop and forecourt on an
OL,10,Fadjacent site as "insensitive," and
OL,11,F"horrendous."
OL,13,FAine Flanagan's partner, Robert Garwe,
OL,14,Fand their 5 year old daughter Shauna
OL,15,Flost their lives in the disaster.
OL,26,@uD@Ar`
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1777065069
OL,3,CCreeslough petrol station plan sparks
OL,4,Canger
OL,6,FAine told UTV the planning approval
OL,7,Fhas been traumatising: "We're not
OL,8,Fopposed to a shop but you know right
OL,9,Fadjacent to where my daughter and her
OL,10,Ffather died and eight other souls....
OL,11,Fthere's great trauma still, everybody,
OL,12,Fthe community, everybody is still
OL,13,Frecovering."
OL,15,FThe first of the appeals was lodged
OL,16,Fwith Ireland's planning authority, An
OL,17,FCoimisiun Pleanala by survivor
OL,18,FChristine Evans.
OL,20,FShe was working in the shop and lived
OL,21,Fin an apartment above.
OL,26,@nD@Ar`oD@XOUuD@LO]yD@HrzyD@Prp
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1777065069
OL,3,CCreeslough petrol station plan sparks
OL,4,Canger
OL,6,FChristine said: "There's no empathy,
OL,7,Fno empathy for these families, no
OL,8,Fempathy whatsoever. "
OL,10,FThis is the second time families and
OL,11,Fsurvivors have campaigned against
OL,12,Fdevelopment plans.
OL,14,FLast year permission for a rebuild on
OL,15,Fthe scene of the disaster was refused.
OL,17,FThose proposals had been submitted by
OL,18,Fa local family who ran the shop and
OL,19,Fowned the site.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1777065069
OL,3,CCreeslough petrol station plan sparks
OL,4,Canger
OL,6,FIt's understood members of that family
OL,7,Fmade this latest application to
OL,8,Fdevelop the adjacent site.
OL,10,FThe proposal includes the demolition
OL,11,Fof an existing house to make way for a
OL,12,Fshop, post office, off-licence, store,
OL,13,Fdeli as well as underground storage
OL,14,Ftanks and fuel pumps.
OL,16,FThe applicants have so far failed to
OL,17,Frespond to a request from UTV for
OL,18,Fcomment.
OL,20,FIt's thought a gas leak may have
OL,21,Fcaused the devastating explosion.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1777065069
OL,3,CCreeslough petrol station plan sparks
OL,4,Canger
OL,6,FFiles have recently been submitted to
OL,7,Fthe Republic's Director of Public
OL,8,FProsecutions by Gardai conducting a
OL,9,Flong running criminal investigation.
OL,11,FSo far no one has been charged.
OL,13,FAine Flanagan says planning
OL,14,Fpermissions should not be granted
OL,15,Funtil all investigations have
OL,16,Fconcluded.
OL,18,FShe said: "There's no reports yet on
OL,19,Fwhat happened, and how it happened and
OL,20,Fwhy it happened.
OL,26,@uD@Ar`zD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1777065069
OL,3,CCreeslough petrol station plan sparks
OL,4,Canger
OL,6,F"How can anyone be allowed to go ahead
OL,7,Fwith planning?"
OL,9,FLegal teams representing a number of
OL,10,Fother victims' relatives and survivors
OL,11,Fhave also lodged appeals.
OL,13,FChristine Evans insists they are
OL,14,Funited in their determination to
OL,15,Foverturn Donegal County council's
OL,16,Fplanning approval.
OL,18,F"We are strong people and we will
OL,19,Ffight to the bitter end."
OL,26,@oD@OO]zD@AOU{D@YO]
